        <main style="background-color:rgba(244, 237, 168, 0.872)">
            <h1 align="center" style="color:rgb(123, 168, 241); font-size: 40px; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-weight: 600;">AURIEA HARVEY AND THE FUTURE OF DIGITAL SCULPTURE </h1>
            <h2 align="center" style="color:rgb(23, 104, 174); font-size: 35px; font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"> Reading Response</h2>
            <h3 align="center" style="color:rgb(10, 71, 123); font-size: 25px; font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;  font-stretch: expanded;"> By Esmeralda Han</h3>   
            <center><img src="https://assets.website-files.com/61e6c06a23cb13bf76051194/62b5f93c1a942265638c8bdc_motherchild-2%20(1).jpg" width="70%"; alt="";></center>
            <details>
                <summary> see here </summary>
            </details>
            <p class="tab" align="center" style="border:solid 1px rgba(42, 42, 219, 0.369); color:rgb(23, 104, 174); font-size: 20px; font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">I have to admit that it is my first time encountering the idea digital sculpture – I mean, it’s so fresh and magical to see these two words make a combination as sculpture in my mind is the most tangible, solid art representation. Only with concrete materials, sculptures can be constructed. Then I soon realize I am partially wrong – establish sculpture through digital ways and establish sculpture in digital is such an attractive form of artistic representation. </p>
            <p class="tab" align="center" style="border:solid 1px rgba(42, 42, 219, 0.369); color:rgb(10, 71, 123); font-size: 20px; font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">In one of Auirea Harvet's statements, she said: "art is polygon." This statement resonates with me because digital sculptures, or any other form of art, exist in a digital realm that is not subject to wear and tear like physical objects. A digital sculpture, however, lacks the tangible, physical presence of a traditional sculpture, and sculpture as an art form has an important physicality.</p>
            <p class="tab" align="center" style="border:solid 1px rgba(42, 42, 219, 0.369); color:rgb(23, 104, 174); font-size: 20px; font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">As technology advances, it opens up new possibilities for artists to explore and express themselves in numerous ways. The integration of technology in art allows for the creation of dynamic and interactive pieces that would not be possible with traditional mediums. </p>
            <p class="tab" align="center" style="border:solid 1px rgba(42, 42, 219, 0.369); color:rgb(10, 71, 123); font-size: 20px; font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">As I film student who sees film’s history, present, and future all developing towards the direction of technology, I am excited to see more applications of digital art. Digital art has the potential to reach a wider audience and to be experienced in unique ways. The use of virtual and augmented reality, for example, allows for the creation of immersive experiences that transport the viewer into the artwork itself. </p>
            </body>

